dutch	The year is 2013.
dutch	The United States government operates the most sophisticated surveillance network in human history.
dutch	Billions of phone calls, emails, and internet sessions are collected, analyzed, and stored — all in the name of national security.
dutch	You are Edward Snowden — NSA contractor, former CIA employee, and the man who is about to make the most consequential decision of his life.
dutch	Your choices in this story mirror the real dilemmas Snowden faced. Some paths lead to freedom. Others lead to ruin.
dutch	Along the way, your knowledge of network security will be tested. Every correct answer moves you closer to the truth.
dutch	REFERENCE DATABASE
dutch	NETWORK SECURITY DOSSIER
dutch	Core cyber-security concepts presented in one scrollable reference layout.
dutch	VPN (Virtual Private Network)
dutch	Creates an encrypted tunnel between your device and a server, hiding your traffic from local network surveillance. Essential on untrusted networks like public Wi-Fi.
dutch	PGP (Pretty Good Privacy)
dutch	Asymmetric encryption system using public/private key pairs. Public key encrypts, only the matching private key can decrypt. Used for secure email communication.
dutch	TOR (The Onion Router)
dutch	Anonymization network that routes traffic through multiple relay nodes, each encrypting a layer. Makes it very difficult to trace traffic to its source.
dutch	HTTPS
dutch	HTTP with TLS/SSL encryption. Secures data between your browser and a web server. Look for the padlock icon in your browser's address bar.
dutch	Firewall
dutch	Network security system that monitors and filters incoming and outgoing traffic based on predefined rules. Acts as a barrier between trusted and untrusted networks.
dutch	Metadata
dutch	Data about data — who you communicated with, when, for how long, from where. Does not include the message content but can reveal intimate patterns of life.
dutch	Man-in-the-Middle Attack
